attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles the upper table from the furniture by unscrewing the 8 screws that hold it. Once unscrewed, the student places each hex socket head on the table one by one. The student proceeds to remove the top table from the furniture, leaving it on the workbench, and then grabs the hex socket heads to stack them on the top table. The student turns the furniture over and begins to unscrew it to remove its legs and in turn places the hex socket heads on the table. The student removes the last leg of the middle tray and places both on the table.

attributes.Transcription: We can now disassemble the side table knarrevik, from IKEA. Please go ahead.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top table of the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the hex socket head on the table.
The student tries to disassemble the table top but is wrong because still has 2 hex socket heads on the furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first leg of the furniture.
The student disassembles the second leg of the furniture.
The student disassembles the third leg of the furniture.
The student disassembles the fourth leg of the furniture.
